g.title: Sheet.160
g.desc: Creating graphics is not part of Advance SVG technique – any ...
g.text: Creating graphics is not part of Advance SVG technique – any graphic software can be used. However, it is necessary that the software can export to SVG format and can attach data to the SVG Group (G) tags.

g.title: Sheet.171
g.desc: ASVG script monitors the document for DIV tags with data-asvg...
g.text: ASVG script monitors the document for DIV tags with data-asvg=”{file_name}.svg” attribute, then it downloads the specified SVG file, modifies it on-the-fly and inserts it into the DOM.

g.title: Sheet.174
g.desc: Marking up shapes is as simple as adding data attributes to t...
g.text: Marking up shapes is as simple as adding data attributes to the SVG Group (G) tag. For example:<g data-asvg-popuplink=”1" …><g data-asvg-popup=”1" ...>make one shape (popuplink), when clicked, to open the other one (popup).

g.title: Sheet.177
g.desc: Publishing a graphic means to make it available on a web serv...
g.text: Publishing a graphic means to make it available on a web server to let ASVG to download and insert it (see step 3).

g.title: Sheet.363
g.desc: Creating a web page is not part of Advance SVG technique – an...
g.text: Creating a web page is not part of Advance SVG technique – any web editing software can be used.

g.title: Sheet.440
g.desc: Adding ASVG Lib is as simple as adding a script tag with a li...
g.text: Adding ASVG Lib is as simple as adding a script tag with a link to CDN source.Advance SVG is Open Source and can be downloaded from GitHub. Also, it can be downloaded as NPM package.

g.title: Sheet.554
g.desc: In practice, creating and managing web content would be withi...
g.text: In practice, creating and managing web content would be within a CMS. Advance SVG is a generic specification, based solely on HTML 5 standards. The technique can be implemented on any CMS; however, each specific systems requires a specific solution.

g.title: Sheet.559
g.desc: Advance SVG does not provide own tools for creating graphics ...
g.text: Advance SVG does not provide own tools for creating graphics – it requires that the graphic software being used can export to SVG format and allows setting data attributes to the shapes.
